Preheat the #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{3} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel).

Halve, peel and slice the @onion{1} as thinly as you can.

Pop the wedges onto a lined #baking tray{}. Toss with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste}, @dried thyme{1%sachet} and a drizzle of @oil{to taste}. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Meanwhile, halve the @cherry tomatoes{125%g}.

Trim the @baby gem{120%g} and separate the leaves. Reserve 1 leaf per person. Thinly slice the remaining lettuce widthways.

To make your dressing, combine @sugar{1/4%tsp} and @oil{2%tbsp} (double both for 4p) in a #medium bowl{}.

Add half the @red wine vinegar{1%sachet} and season with salt and pepper.

Just before serving, add the sliced baby gem and tomatoes to the dressing and toss to coat.

== Burgers ==

To a #large bowl{}, add the @Irish beef mince{250%g}, @breadcrumbs{1%pack}, @salt{1/2%tsp} and @water{2%tbsp} (double both for 4p). Season with pepper and mix together by hand.

Roll into balls then shape into 1cm thick burgers—1 per person.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

When the wedges are halfway cooked, place the burgers on a lined baking tray. Cook on the middle shelf until browned, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> TIP: Burgers may shrink slightly during cooking.

== Caramelised Onions and Bacon ==

Meanwhile, place a pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, lay in the @Irish bacon{170%g} and fry until crispy and brown, ~{3-4%minutes} on each side. Once cooked, transfer to a #plate{} lined with #kitchen paper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Cook bacon thoroughly.

Return the pan to medium heat with a drizzle of oil.

Once hot, add the onion and fry, stirring occasionally, until softened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Once softened, add @sugar{1%tsp} (double for 4p) and the remaining @red wine vinegar{1%sachet} to the onion.

Reduce the heat and cook until soft and sticky, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from the heat.

== Assembly ==

Meanwhile, place the @grated cheese{50%g} on top of the cooked burgers and pop back into the oven until the cheese has melted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Pop the @brioche buns{2} into the oven to warm through at the same time, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When everything is ready, spread a layer of caramelised onion over each bun base.

Top with the cheesy burgers, crispy bacon and reserved baby gem leaves.

Sandwich shut with the bun lids.

Toss the wedges in the @truffle oil{1%pack}.

Serve your cheesy bacon burgers with wedges and salad alongside.